  "response_text": "# Weight Management Plan for Frequent Business Travelers\n\n## Core Strategy: Consistency Over Perfection\n\nSince routines are disrupted, focus on **non-negotiable habits** rather than rigid meal plans.\n\n---\n\n## Nutrition Strategies\n\n### Before Travel\n- **Meal prep snacks** for flights/car rides (nuts, protein bars, fruit)\n- Research restaurant options at your destination\n- Download a food tracking app for easy logging on-the-go\n\n### During Travel\n**Hotel room essentials:**\n- Instant oatmeal, nuts, protein powder\n- Resistance bands or workout videos (no equipment needed)\n\n**Restaurant dining:**\n- Scan menus online before arriving\n- Order protein + vegetables + whole grain\n- Request dressings/sauces on the side\n- Avoid \"all-you-can-eat\" buffets\n\n**Quick wins:**\n- Choose hotels with gyms or near parks\n- Walk instead of using shuttles when possible\n- Stay hydrated (often mistaken for hunger)\n\n---\n\n## Exercise Plan\n\n### Realistic Approach\n- **15-20 minutes daily** beats skipping workouts entirely\n- No gym required: bodyweight exercises in your room\n\n**Sample routine:**\n- 5 min warm-up (jumping jacks, stretching)\n- 10 min strength (push-ups, squats, lunges)\n- 5 min cardio (burpees, high knees)\n\n### Alternatives\n- Hotel gym or local gym day pass\n- Running/walking routes\n- Yoga or stretching videos\n\n---\n\n## Tracking & Accountability\n\n- **Weekly weigh-ins** (same day/time) rather than daily\n- Track protein intake (most satiating macronutrient)\n- Use a habit tracker for consistency, not perfection\n- Monthly photo/measurement checks\n\n---\n\n## Sleep & Stress\n\n- Maintain consistent sleep schedule despite time zones\n- Limit alcohol (empty calories + poor sleep)\n- Practice stress management (meditation apps, walks)\n\n---\n\n## Realistic Expectations\n\n- Aim for **maintenance or slow loss** (0.5-1 lb/week)\n- Plan for 1-2 higher-calorie days per week\n- Focus on **not gaining** during travel months\n\nWould you like me to customize this for specific travel patterns or dietary preferences?",
